@node Main "InterBall - Documentation"

                            'InterBall' 1.01

                           by Charles-N. Jacob

  'InterBall' is a Workbench @{" game " link play} which is played on an 8 by 8
space board, filled with 4 different sizes and colours of balls.
The idea is to burst as many balls of the same colour that are
located next to each other, as possible... and the more balls you
burst, the more points you will get.

  One thing to remember, to burst a ball, it must be at its maximum
size, otherwise, clicking on it will increase its size. There are
no restriction other than that, maybe some blocks will appear and
be in the way when they are not needed, but such is this game. By
the way, can you burst an entire board full of same coloured balls?
If you do, you will be rewarded with 3782 points!

  Have fun!

