@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'InterBall' where you want
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must
have 8 colours or more.

                             How to play?

  At the start of the game, the board is filled with balls of 4
different sizes and colours. To play the game, click on any ball,
if the ball is at its maximum size, it will then burst, otherwise
it will increase in size. If a ball burst and there are surrounding
balls of the same size and colour, they will also burst, and so on,
making a chain reaction.

  The goal is to burst at least 3 balls of the same colour, when
those balls burst, balls or other objects located above will fall
in the emptied spaces. The more balls you burst, the more points
you get, as shown on the following table:

  3 balls = 1 point
  4 balls = 2 points
  5 balls = 6 points
  6 balls = 12 points
          .
          .
  12 balls = 90 points
          .
          .
  64 balls = 3782 points

  Watch out for the 'gauge' shown at the right of the game board;
the number of coloured rectangles indicates how many balls are
surrounded by 2 or more balls of the same colour. If that number
exceeds 8, a white '+' sign will appear on the uppermost part of
the gauge. On the other hand, if the gauge gets empty, the game
will be over.

  The game keeps the best score made since it was run.

  Have fun!

